8#include "webm/buffer_reader.h"

10#include <algorithm>
11#include <cassert>
12#include <cstddef>
13#include <cstdint>

20namespace webm {
21
22BufferReader::BufferReader(std::initializer_list<std::uint8_t> bytes)
23 : data_(bytes) {}
24
25BufferReader::BufferReader(const std::vector<std::uint8_t>& vector)
26 : data_(vector) {}
27
28BufferReader::BufferReader(std::vector<std::uint8_t>&& vector)
29 : data_(std::move(vector)) {}
30
31BufferReader::BufferReader(BufferReader&& other)
32 : data_(std::move(other.data_)), pos_(other.pos_) {
33 other.pos_ = 0;
34}
35
36BufferReader& BufferReader::operator=(BufferReader&& other) {
37 if (this != &other) {
38 data_ = std::move(other.data_);
39 pos_ = other.pos_;
40 other.pos_ = 0;
41 }
42 return *this;
43}
44
45BufferReader& BufferReader::operator=(
46 std::initializer_list<std::uint8_t> bytes) {
47 data_ = std::vector<std::uint8_t>(bytes);
48 pos_ = 0;
49 return *this;
50}
51
52Status BufferReader::Read(std::size_t num_to_read, std::uint8_t* buffer,
53 std::uint64_t* num_actually_read) {
54 assert(num_to_read > 0);
55 assert(buffer != nullptr);
56 assert(num_actually_read != nullptr);
57
58 *num_actually_read = 0;
59 std::size_t expected = num_to_read;
60
61 std::size_t num_remaining = data_.size() - pos_;
62 if (num_remaining == 0) {
63 return Status(Status::kEndOfFile);
64 }
65
66 if (num_to_read > num_remaining) {
67 num_to_read = static_cast<std::size_t>(num_remaining);
68 }
69
70 std::copy_n(data_.data() + pos_, num_to_read, buffer);
71 *num_actually_read = num_to_read;
72 pos_ += num_to_read;
73
74 if (*num_actually_read != expected) {
75 return Status(Status::kOkPartial);
76 }
77
78 return Status(Status::kOkCompleted);
79}
80
81Status BufferReader::Skip(std::uint64_t num_to_skip,
82 std::uint64_t* num_actually_skipped) {
83 assert(num_to_skip > 0);
84 assert(num_actually_skipped != nullptr);
85
86 *num_actually_skipped = 0;
87 std::uint64_t expected = num_to_skip;
88
89 std::size_t num_remaining = data_.size() - pos_;
90 if (num_remaining == 0) {
91 return Status(Status::kEndOfFile);
92 }
93
94 if (num_to_skip > num_remaining) {
95 num_to_skip = static_cast<std::uint64_t>(num_remaining);
96 }
97
98 *num_actually_skipped = num_to_skip;
99 pos_ += num_to_skip;
100
101 if (*num_actually_skipped != expected) {
102 return Status(Status::kOkPartial);
103 }
104
105 return Status(Status::kOkCompleted);
106}
107
108std::uint64_t BufferReader::Position() const { return pos_; }
